The paper deals with cross-modal retrieval tasks involving images and text, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also proposes a deep learning framework, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically deep learning (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) as it deals with text data, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper also involves multimedia analysis (cs.MM) as it deals with multiple modalities such as images and text.
